<paragraph id="8BD00269FFF8C820FF5BFC7FFDFAB7C9" blockId="19.[151,624,942,969]" box="[151,624,942,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<heading id="D098B505FFF8C820FF5BFC7FFDFAB7C9" bold="true" box="[151,624,942,969]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FF5BFC7FFDFAB7C9" authority="Ehrenberg, 1831" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1831" box="[151,624,942,969]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Trichodinidae" genus="Trichodina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pediculus">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF5BFC7FFDFAB7C9" bold="true" box="[151,624,942,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF5BFC7FFE13B7C8" bold="true" box="[151,409,942,969]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Trichodina pediculus</emphasis>
Ehrenberg, 1831
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD00269FFF8C820FF5BFC27FB60B0C5" blockId="19.[151,1437,1014,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF5BFC27FDA2B011" bold="true" box="[151,552,1014,1040]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Record as epibiont on cnidarians:</emphasis>
The species was found (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FCF4FC27FB8CB010" author="James-Clark, H." box="[824,1030,1014,1041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="401 - 425" refId="ref15447" refString="James-Clark, H. (1866) On the anatomy and physiology of the vorticellidan parasite (Trichodina pediculus, Erh.) of Hydra. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, including Zoology, Botany and Geology, Series 3, VIII, 52, 401 - 425. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222936608679570" type="journal article" year="1866">James-Clark 1866</bibRefCitation>
) on the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FB93FC27FA16B011" authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[1119,1436,1014,1040]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Hydridae" genus="Hydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="oligactis">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FB93FC27FA87B011" box="[1119,1293,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Hydra oligactis</emphasis>
Pallas, 1766
</taxonomicName>
(mentioned under synonymic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FDEAFBCBFD25B035" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[550,687,1050,1076]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Hydridae" genus="Hydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FDEAFBCBFD25B035" box="[550,687,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Hydra fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FD21FBCAFB87B035" authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[749,1037,1050,1076]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Hydridae" genus="Hydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="viridisima">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FD21FBCAFC0AB035" box="[749,896,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">H. viridisima</emphasis>
Pallas, 1766
</taxonomicName>
(mentioned under synonymic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FF5BFBEFFEA5B059" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[151,303,1086,1112]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Hydridae" genus="Hydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF5BFBEFFEA5B059" box="[151,303,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Hydra viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Later the species was observed on the medusa stage of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FC71FBEFFAD4B059" authority="Annandale, 1912" authorityName="Annandale" authorityYear="1912" box="[957,1374,1086,1112]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Trichodinidae" genus="Lymnocnida" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FC71FBEFFB1FB059" box="[957,1173,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Lymnocnida indica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FB51FBEFFAD4B059" author="Annandale, N." box="[1181,1374,1086,1112]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="253 - 256" refId="ref11929" refString="Annandale, N. (1912) Preliminary description of a freshwater medusa from Bombay Presidency. Records of the Indian Museum, 7, 253 - 256. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 28235" type="journal article" year="1912">Annandale, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Tambi in the Koyna valley in the Satara district of the 
<collectingCountry id="F37842F9FFF8C820FD3EFBB3FCDBB07D" box="[754,849,1122,1148]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Mumbai</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="F37842F9FFF8C820FC93FBB3FC4BB07C" box="[863,961,1122,1149]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Bombay</collectingCountry>
) Presidency, 
<collectingCountry id="F37842F9FFF8C820FB99FBB3FB05B07D" box="[1109,1167,1122,1148]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FB51FBB3FAD3B07D" author="Annandale, N." box="[1181,1369,1122,1148]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="253 - 256" refId="ref11929" refString="Annandale, N. (1912) Preliminary description of a freshwater medusa from Bombay Presidency. Records of the Indian Museum, 7, 253 - 256. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 28235" type="journal article" year="1912">Annandale 1912</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FAA9FBB2FEE8B0A1" author="Martonelli, S. R. &amp; Marcotegui, P. S. &amp; Alda, P." pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="257 - 261" refId="ref16053" refString="Martonelli, S. R., Marcotegui, P. S. &amp; Alda, P. (2008) Trichodina marplatensis sp. n. (Ciliophora: Trichodinidae) from Combjelly, Mnemiopsis mccradyi (Mayer, 1900) in Argentine Sea. Acta Protozoologica, 47, 257 - 261." type="journal article" year="2008">
Martonelli 
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF2AFB56FE9DB0A1" box="[230,279,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was also reported on freshwater hydromedusa (Jellyfish) 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FB44FB57FEC0B0C5" authority="Lankester, 1880" authorityName="Lankester" authorityYear="1880" class="Hydrozoa" family="Olindiidae" genus="Craspedacusta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Limnomedusae" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sowerbyi">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FB44FB57FA16B0A1" box="[1160,1436,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Craspedacusta sowerbyi</emphasis>
Lankester, 1880
</taxonomicName>
collected from a pond near Heidelberg, 
<collectingCountry id="F37842F9FFF8C820FCC2FB7BFCFCB0C5" box="[782,886,1194,1220]" name="Germany" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FC49FB7BFB57B0C5" author="Hausmann, K. &amp; Hausmann, E." box="[901,1245,1194,1221]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="131 - 143" refId="ref15159" refString="Hausmann, K. &amp; Hausmann, E. (1981) Structural studies on Trichodina pediculus (Ciliophora, Peritricha) I. The locomotor fringe and the oral apparatus. Journal of ultrastructure research, 74, 131 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0022 - 5320 (81) 80071 - 8" type="journal article" year="1981">Hausmann &amp; Hausmann 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37551E2FFF8C820FF0BFB1FFE3FB10C" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD00269FFF8C820FF0BFB1FFE3FB10C" blockId="19.[151,1437,1014,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF0BFB1FFDD6B0E9" bold="true" box="[199,604,1230,1256]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Record as epibiont on other hosts:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FDAFFB1FFCC5B0E9" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1831" box="[611,847,1230,1256]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Trichodinidae" genus="Trichodina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pediculus">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FDAFFB1FFCC5B0E9" box="[611,847,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Trichodina pediculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also found parasiting on a wide range of fish species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FF52FB23FE22B10C" author="Van As, J. G. &amp; Basson, L." box="[158,424,1266,1293]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="76 - 78" refId="ref18617" refString="Van As, J. G. &amp; Basson, L. (1986) A new species of Trichodina (Ciliophora: Peritricha) from limnocnidid medusa in the Zambezy system. South African Journal of Zoology, 21, 76 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 02541858.1986.11447961" type="journal article" year="1986">Van As &amp; Basson 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37551E2FFF8C820FF0BFAC7FC42B155" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD00269FFF8C820FF0BFAC7FC42B155" blockId="19.[151,1437,1014,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FF0BFAC7FEB7B131" bold="true" box="[199,317,1302,1328]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FE88FAC7FD84B131" author="Annandale, N." box="[324,526,1302,1328]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="253 - 256" refId="ref11929" refString="Annandale, N. (1912) Preliminary description of a freshwater medusa from Bombay Presidency. Records of the Indian Museum, 7, 253 - 256. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 28235" type="journal article" year="1912">Annandale (1912)</bibRefCitation>
has not described or pictured the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F79EAFFF8C820FC4FFAC6FB83B131" authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1831" box="[899,1033,1302,1328]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Trichodinidae" genus="Trichodina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pediculus">
<emphasis id="B91BDE7BFFF8C820FC4FFAC6FB83B131" box="[899,1033,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">T. pediculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found on medusa. Hence, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE7F98FFF8C820FAFDFAC6FEB0B154" author="Van As, J. G. &amp; Basson, L." pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="76 - 78" refId="ref18617" refString="Van As, J. G. &amp; Basson, L. (1986) A new species of Trichodina (Ciliophora: Peritricha) from limnocnidid medusa in the Zambezy system. South African Journal of Zoology, 21, 76 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 02541858.1986.11447961" type="journal article" year="1986">Van As &amp; Basson (1986)</bibRefCitation>
believed that the Annandale’s identification was doubtful.
</paragraph>
